{"body": "An individual who makes a claim is entitled to a personal allowance of \u00a312,570 for a tax year if the individual meets the requirements of section 56 (residence etc).\nFor an individual whose adjusted net income exceeds \u00a3100,000, the allowance under subsection (1) is reduced by one-half of the excess.\nIf the amount of any allowance that remains after the operation of subsection (2) would otherwise not be a multiple of \u00a31, it is to be rounded up to the nearest amount which is a multiple of \u00a31.\nFor the meaning of \u201cadjusted net income\u201d see section 58.", "citation_label": "2007 c. 3 s. 35", "citation_path": "uk/statute/ukpga/2007/3/35", "document_class": "statute", "expression_date": "2026-05-29", "heading": "Section 35", "id": "9c62a512-657f-5768-a7d7-162d9f6b3370", "identifiers": {"legislation.gov.uk:number": "3", "legislation.gov.uk:provision": "35", "legislation.gov.uk:type": "ukpga", "legislation.gov.uk:year": "2007"}, "jurisdiction": "uk", "kind": "section", "language": "en", "legal_identifier": "2007 c. 3 s. 35", "level": 1, "metadata": {"extent": ["E", "W", "S", "N.I."], "references_to": ["ukpga/2007/3", "ukpga/2007/3", "ukpga/2007/3", "ukpga/2007/3", "ukpga/2007/3", "ukpga/2007/3", "ukpga/2007/3", "ukpga/2007/3", "ukpga/2007/3", "ukpga/2007/3", "ukpga/2007/3", "ukpga/2007/3", "ukpga/2007/3", "ukpga/2007/3", "ukpga/2007/3", "ukpga/2007/3", "ukpga/2007/3"], "retrieved_at": null}, "ordinal": 35, "parent_citation_path": "uk/statute/ukpga/2007/3", "parent_id": "5f997f9f-2565-5c6f-9db6-1810c0d15f9d", "source_as_of": "2026-05-29", "source_document_id": "ukpga/2007/3", "source_format": "legislation.gov.uk-clml", "source_id": "http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/2007/3/section/35", "source_path": "sources/uk/statute/2026-05-29-uk-pe-parity/ukpga/2007/3/section-35.xml", "source_url": "http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/2007/3/section/35", "version": "2026-05-29-uk-pe-parity"}
